  [PARTIAL] Split
    Evidence: GameEngine.playerSplit() (GameEngine.java:219-253),
              GameController.onHit() (GameController.java:183-208)
    The split initiation in GameEngine is correct: validates same-rank pair,
    charges same-bet cost, removes second card, deals one card to each hand.
    ISSUE: When the player hits on a split hand, GameController.onHit()
    directly calls `engine.getGameState().getDeck().drawCard()` and
    `activeHand.addCard(card)` instead of calling `engine.playerHit()`.
    This bypasses the engine's turn validation entirely. If validation
    were ever tightened, split hits would silently pass through unchecked.
    Additionally, TurnManager has no concept of split hands at all —
    split turn management lives entirely in the controller.

  [PASS] Bust detection, win/loss/draw resolution
    Evidence: Hand.isBusted(), BlackjackRules.determineWinnerSP/MP()
    SP: player bust → DEALER_WINS immediately. Dealer bust → PLAYER_WINS.
    Natural BJ → BLACKJACK result, 3:2 payout (multiplier 2.5x).
    Equal scores → PUSH. MP: both bust → PUSH. One bust → other wins.
    BJ beats regular 21. All cases covered correctly.

  [PASS] PvP — opponent card visibility enforced
